Preamble

The CERN Open Hardware Licence (CERN-OHL) is a legal tool to facilitate the sharing of hardware designs. It is inspired by free and open source software licences. The CERN-OHL comes in three variants: CERN-OHL-S (Strongly Reciprocal), CERN-OHL-W (Weakly Reciprocal) and CERN-OHL-P (Permissive).

This licence is CERN-OHL-S, the Strongly Reciprocal variant. It is designed for use with hardware designs, including documentation, software, and other materials related to the hardware.

Hardware design is a creative process, and the resulting designs may be protected by copyright and other laws. This licence does not grant any rights under patent law. However, it does grant a licence to the copyright in the design.

The spirit of this licence is to allow the design to be shared and modified freely, and to encourage collaboration. The reciprocal nature of this licence requires that any modifications to the design are also shared under the same terms. This ensures that the community as a whole benefits from the work of its members.

1. Definitions

1.1. 'Licence' means this CERN-OHL-S v2.

1.2. 'Source' means information that is preferred for making modifications to the design. It may be in the form of text files, drawings, schematics, computer-aided design (CAD) data, or any other format that is suitable for editing.

1.3. 'Covered Source' means Source that is explicitly made available under this Licence.

1.4. 'Product' means any device, component, or system that is made using the design, whether in whole or in part.

1.5. 'Licensor' means the person or entity that distributes the Covered Source under this Licence.

1.6. 'You' means any person or entity that exercises any of the rights granted by this Licence.

2. Licence Grant

2.1. The Licensor hereby grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, perpetual licence to do the following, subject to the terms and conditions of this Licence:

    a. to study the Covered Source;
    b. to modify the Covered Source;
    c. to copy and distribute the Covered Source and any modifications you make to it;
    d. to make Products based on the Covered Source and any modifications you make to it;
    e. to use, sell, or otherwise dispose of Products you make.

2.2. This Licence does not grant any rights under patent law.

3. Conditions

3.1. If you distribute Covered Source, you must provide a copy of this Licence with it.

3.2. If you distribute Covered Source that you have modified, you must:

    a. make the modified Covered Source available under this Licence;
    b. include a notice stating that you have modified the Covered Source and the date of the modification;
    c. ensure that the modified Covered Source is in a format that is preferred for making modifications.

3.3. Any distribution of Covered Source must include a notice stating that the source is available from a specific location, and how to access it. This may be a link to a version control repository, a website, or any other means of access.

4. Disclaimer of Warranty

The Covered Source is provided 'as is', without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose and non-infringement. In no event shall the authors or copyright holders be liable for any claim, damages or other liability, whether in an action of contract, tort or otherwise, arising from, out of or in connection with the Covered Source or the use or other dealings in the Covered Source.

5. Limitation of Liability

In no event shall the Licensor be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, exemplary, or consequential damages (including, but not limited to, procurement of substitute goods or services; loss of use, data, or profits; or business interruption) however caused and on any theory of liability, whether in contract, strict liability, or tort (including negligence or otherwise) arising in any way out of the use of this Covered Source, even if advised of the possibility of such damage.

6. Termination

6.1. This Licence will terminate automatically if you fail to comply with any of its terms and conditions.

6.2. If this Licence is terminated, your rights under it will be reinstated if you come into compliance with the terms and conditions.

7. General

7.1. This Licence is the entire agreement between you and the Licensor concerning the subject matter hereof.

7.2. If any provision of this Licence is held to be unenforceable, such provision shall be reformed only to the extent necessary to make it enforceable.

7.3. This Licence shall be governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which the Licensor is located, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
